### Did you use AI tools?
`Yes`

#### Describe which AI tools you used, what you used them for, and what you learned. 200 words or less.
I used Cursor, ChatGPT, and Gemini. Cursor was used for coding, while ChatGPT and Gemini were employed for both coding and generating ideas. By also brainstorming with ChatGPT and Gemini, it became easier to come up with ideas.
When coding with AI, Swift's syntax is very natural and close to English, making it highly understandable. Furthermore, SwiftUI was particularly useful for leveraging AI, as it allows layouts to be easily constructed simply by writing code. I have been learning Swift since Year 8 and can handle basic coding independently. Additionally, utilising AI for coding not only increases development efficiency but also enables me to quickly learn the knowledge needed to realise what I want to create.
When undertaking complex implementations, I encountered the challenge of accurately conveying my vision to the AI. Consequently, when issuing instructions, I made a conscious effort to avoid ambiguous or abstract expressions, instead employing logical explanations that drew upon my knowledge of mathematics and physics. This experience taught me how to communicate my ideas to the AI in detail.


### What other technologies did you use in your app playground, and why did you choose them? 200 words or less.
We adopted SwiftUI, a declarative UI framework, as the core of our UI to ensure development speed and consistency in state management. Meanwhile, we bridge and utilize UIKit for areas requiring advanced customization or existing assets.
To handle state transitions reactively, we primarily adopted Combine for state synchronization and timer-driven logic using @Published and sink/assign. For asynchronous processing, we combined Swift Concurrency to safely perform state updates primarily on the main actor.
To deliver high-quality audio and video experiences, the onboarding video was implemented using AVPlayer/AVPlayerLayer, with playback primarily built on AVFoundation.
For the confetti effect during clearing, we introduced 3D rendering using SceneKit. This enables dynamic visual effects impossible to achieve with 2D alone.


