## Comments (optional)
### Is there anything else you‘d like us to know?
Since encountering Swift in my second year of junior high school, I've been captivated by the joy of bringing ideas to life through programming. I've always found happiness in shaping and expressing my experiences and passions, then sharing them with others. For me, programming isn't just a skill—it's a powerful means of communicating myself and my experiences.
The core of this project is reviving fading traditions through an app. Ohajiki is a wonderful part of Japanese culture, yet it's losing its place in modern times. My goal is to use Swift to pass on these ohajiki games to the next generation with my own hands.
I hope this app becomes a bridge connecting tradition and technology, the previous generation and the next.
Nothing would make me happier than continuing to share my wonderful experiences with others through apps.

